-- A Third of Spaniards See Euro Exit as Positive, ABC Survey Shows
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-04-29T13:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/a-third-of-spaniards-see-euro-exit-as-positive-abc-survey-shows.html
A Spanish decision to leave the
euro would be positive for the country, according to a third of
people polled for a survey in  ABC  newspaper.  About 54 percent said a Spanish exit would be negative
compared with 33.5 percent who would view it as economically
positive, according to a DYM survey for the Madrid-based
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
